push

public void push(com.conceptwave.scripting.Object breadCrumbObject,
                 com.conceptwave.scripting.Object linkLabel,
                 com.conceptwave.scripting.Boolean isMulti,
                 com.conceptwave.scripting.Integer selectedIndex)
Can be any type of scriptable object

Parameters:
breadCrumbObject - The breadcrumb object to push, can be a single object, or an array of objects. In the case of an array, the breadcrumb link will be displayed as a drop down menu rather than a single link. The order of menu items will be the same order as the objects in the array. The parameter selectedIndex will indicate the index of the current selection
linkLabel - The label or resourceId that will be displayed as part of the breadcrumb. If valid resourceId, then it translates into current language. Otherwise, displays as label. if null, then default logic will attempt to get a label from the breadCrumbObject: If breadCrumbObject is instance of CwfDataObject: its label will be used. For all other types of objects, its toString() method will be used. If breadCrumbObject is an array, then the linkLabel should be an array of equal length or null.
isMulti - true, if breadCrumbObject is an array. If false, breadCrumbObject is treated as single object, even if an array.
selectedIndex: - The index of the current selection if breadCrumbObject is an array. If empty, the default index 0 is used.
